						<td>
							<div style="width: 230px; float: left; position: relative;">
								<a href="site.do?siteId=71">International Comparisons of Living Standards by Equivalent Incomes</a><br/>
								<div class="loupe">
									<a href="#abstractPaper-71" rel="abstractPaper71" title="Details of the article">
										<img alt="" src="images/icones/loupe.gif" />
									</a>
									<!-- Abstract publication -->
									<div id="abstractPaper-71" class="abstract-paper">
										<div class="top-abstract-paper">
											<div class="top-left-abstract-paper">Abstract</div>
											<div class="top-right-abstract-paper">Close</div>
										</div>
										<div class="abstract-separate-line"></div>
										<div class="middle-abstract-paper">
											<!-- description du site -->
											We propose a measure of living standards for international comparisons. Based on GDP per
capita, the measure incorporates corrections for international flows of income, labor, risk of
unemployment, healthy life expectancy, household demography and inequalities. The method
for comparing populations that differ in some non-income dimension consists of computing
the equivalent variation of income that would make each population indifferent between its
current situation and a reference situation with respect to the non-income dimension. This is
applied to 24 OECD countries. The obtained ranking of countries differs substantially from
the GDP ranking.
